<bioghist encodinganalog="545"><p>Carmen A. Roberts was a member of the Detroit school board and a leader of the anti-busing movement in Detroit in the mid-1970s.</p></bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520"><p>The Roberts papers document her activities in the anti-busing movement in the Detroit area in the mid-1970s.  The papers include correspondence, speeches, clippings, legal brief, organizational miscellanea, and collected pro- and anti-busing materials.  There are also photographs of anti-busing demonstrations and a motion picture film of 1976 anti-busing rally.</p></scopecontent>

